<TITLE> US offers anti-terror training to RAB </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 20 (bdnews24.com)The United States is prepared to offer anti-terrorism training to members of Rapid Action Battalion, US ambassador James F Moriarty said Thursday. Moriarty made the offer as he called on foreign minister Dipu Moni at her foreign ministry office, said a statement by the Press Information Department. "James F Moriarty informed the foreign minister that the United States government would extend their cooperation to the sectors of anti-terrorism and training to RAB members," said the statement. "Bangladesh maintains zero tolerance for religious extremism," it quoted Dipu Moni as saying. Dipu Moni also mentioned that the government had been pursuing those who were involved in extremism activities and some JMB suspects gad already been arrested from various parts of the country, said the PID. The foreign minister, it said, informed the envoy that Bangladesh would host a three-day workshop on November 8 to 10 for the police officers of South Asian countries.
